---
import BaseLayout from "../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Mainline vs RAG"
  description="RAG helps coding agents find similar code. Mainline helps them understand historical engineering intent before editing."
>
  <section class="page-hero shell compact">
    <p class="eyebrow">Comparison</p>
    <h1>Mainline vs RAG</h1>
    <p>
      Code retrieval is useful. It is not the same thing as repo memory.
    </p>
  </section>

  <section class="section shell comparison-table">
    <div class="comparison-row header">
      <span></span>
      <span>RAG</span>
      <span>Mainline</span>
    </div>
    <div class="comparison-row">
      <span>Best at</span>
      <span>Finding relevant code and documents</span>
      <span>Recording decisions, risks, anti-patterns, and lifecycle</span>
    </div>
    <div class="comparison-row">
      <span>Timing</span>
      <span>Usually used during code inspection</span>
      <span>Required before non-trivial edits</span>
    </div>
    <div class="comparison-row">
      <span>Failure mode</span>
      <span>Retrieves the abandoned Redis implementation</span>
      <span>Explains why Redis was abandoned</span>
    </div>
    <div class="comparison-row">
      <span>System of record</span>
      <span>Vector store or vendor index</span>
      <span>Git refs and notes owned by the repo</span>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
